# PowerShell Patterns for mJig

## Script Scope

Parameters are copied to `$script:` variables (PowerShell params are read-only). Nested functions must use `$script:` prefix to modify persistent state.

## LogArray (CRITICAL)

`$LogArray` is a `System.Collections.Generic.List[object]`, NOT a plain array.

```powershell
# CORRECT
$null = $LogArray.Add([PSCustomObject]@{
    logRow = $true
    components = @(
        @{ priority = 1; text = "full"; shortText = "short" }
    )
})

# WRONG — wipes entire log every call
if ($LogArray -isnot [Array]) { $LogArray = @() }
$LogArray += [PSCustomObject]@{ ... }
```

Never use `= @()` or `+=` on `$LogArray`. No guard needed — render loop trims to `$Rows` automatically.

## Collection Allocation (Hot Path)

Pre-allocated collections must be cleared/reused, never recreated:
- `$intervalMouseInputs` (`HashSet[string]`) — use `.Clear()` and `$null = .Add(...)`, never `+=`
- `$script:MenuItemsBounds` (`List[hashtable]`) — use `.Clear()` and `.Add()`
- `$pressedMenuKeys` (hashtable) — use `.Clear()`
- `$_waitPeekBuffer` (`INPUT_RECORD[]`) — reuse as-is

## Encoding (CRITICAL)

Box-drawing characters must use `[char]` casts, never literals (prevents encoding corruption):

```powershell
$char = [char]0x250C  # SAFE
$char = "┌"           # RISKY — corrupts if encoding changes
```

## ReadKey Gotcha

Never use `ReadKey("IncludeKeyDown")` alone — it blocks on KeyUp events. Always use:
```powershell
$Host.UI.RawUI.ReadKey("NoEcho,IncludeKeyDown,IncludeKeyUp,AllowCtrlC")
```
Filter KeyDown/KeyUp in code after the read.

## GetDate in Hot Path

`$date = Get-Date` is refreshed each 50ms tick. Use `$date.ToString("HH:mm:ss")` — don't call `(Get-Date)` again.
